{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:58:37.918411", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview of network health\\n- Control-plane across the fabric is healthy. All EBGP peerings between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging expected routes.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 BGP: 4 peers up; receiving 7 prefixes; routing table includes 10.0.1.0/24 via spine and all other /24s.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 BGP: 4 peers up; receiving 7 prefixes; connected 10.0.1.0/24; full reachability to other /24s via spine.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1 BGP: peers with super-spine and leaves are up; ECMP routes toward 10.1.x/24 and proper next-hops for 10.0.x/24s.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 BGP: all spine neighbors up; receiving/sending expected prefixes.\\n- General reachability in the fabric (excluding one host) appears normal based on successful pings between other hosts/subnets.\\n\\nDetected anomaly\\n- Host pc_0_0 is isolated/unreachable.\\n  - Ping from pc_0_0 to pc_0_1 fails: “Network is unreachable.”\\n  - Ping from pc_0_1 to pc_0_0 times out.\\n  - Ping from leaf_router_0_0 (default gateway for pc_0_0’s subnet) to pc_0_0 times out.\\n\\nLocalization of the fault\\n- The issue is localized to host pc_0_0 and its access link toward leaf_router_0_0.\\n  - pc_0_0 network interface state:\\n    - eth0 has IP 10.0.0.2/24 but is DOWN (ip addr shows state DOWN).\\n    - ethtool reports “Link detected: no” on eth0.\\n    - No RX/TX traffic recorded; no kernel routes present (ip route empty), consistent with a downed interface.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 access interface toward host:\\n    - eth4 is up with 10.0.0.1/24 (default gateway).\\n    - ARP table shows 10.0.0.2 lladdr 62:e5:4c:0b:77:28 in STALE state; attempts to ping pc_0_0 from the leaf time out, indicating no L2/L3 responsiveness from the host side.\\n\\nImpact scope\\n- Only pc_0_0 is impacted. Host pc_0_1 and the rest of the fabric show normal connectivity and routing.\\n- The fabric’s EBGP routes for 10.0.0.0/24 are installed across the network (i.e., the control-plane is advertising/accepting the subnet), but the data-plane cannot reach pc_0_0 due to its link being down.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Physical/administrative link-down on pc_0_0’s NIC (eth0). Evidence: interface state DOWN and “Link detected: no” on pc_0_0, with corresponding lack of L2/L3 reachability from its leaf router. The empty routing table on pc_0_0 is a consequence of the interface being down (connected route not installed), rather than a separate control-plane fault.\\n\\nRelevant evidence (highlights)\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - ip addr: eth0 state DOWN; inet 10.0.0.2/24.\\n  - ethtool eth0: Link detected: no.\\n  - ip route: empty.\\n- leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - Interface toward host: eth4 10.0.0.1/24 UP.\\n  - ip neigh: 10.0.0.2 lladdr 62:e5:4c:0b:77:28 STALE.\\n  - ping 10.0.0.2: timeout.\\n  - BGP summary: all peers up, receiving 7 prefixes, routing table includes all expected /24s.\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - eth0 UP with 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1; normal TX/RX; successful reachability elsewhere in the fabric.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The data center fabric and EBGP control-plane are operating normally.\\n- The only identified anomaly is the host pc_0_0’s access link being down, isolating that host from the network., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='11c1ef55-3fb7-4d55-9166-c562e7dcc419'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
